<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">I) When the Policy Applies</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This loot policy will be in effect for any OWD event at which 2 or more groups of OWD members are present and is led by an OWD member. <br>
<br>
If OWD and another guild conduct a truly joint raid this policy will not apply. However, if OWD simply invites members of another guild to attend and OWD does all the running of the raid, it will be considered an OWD event and the policy will apply. <br>
<br>
The policy does not apply to the WToV series of Raids. Those raids will continue to operate on their <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub43.ezboard.com/forderofthewhitedragon33013frm1.showMessage?topicID=101.topic" target="top">current loot rules</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> unless and until changes are announced. Any unscheduled raid in WToV which has the primary purpose of killing named MOBs does fall under this loot policy.<br>
<br>
Loot is distributed by named BGH MOB. A seperate named MOB, even if back to back, or in the same zone is a new event for loot purposes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">II) Master Looter</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The guild will not have a designated ML, rather the major raid leader members of the raid team will alternate as ML. The acting ML will make all final decisions on who is eligible to enter NBG rolls.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">III) Defaults</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Non-epic loot may be defaulted in order to best provide for the guild's continued advancement. <br>
<br>
These defaults will be decided after the loot drops are known and be made by the major raid leaders present at the time. If none of the major raid leaders are present at the time that loot is distributed then no loot may be defaulted. <br>
<br>
If only 1 items drops, it will not be defaulted, unless it was a predetermined and announced default on a mob known to drop only one item.<br>
<br>
If the number of items dropped by the MOB is two to four then 1 item may be defaulted. <br>
<br>
If the number of the items dropped by the MOB is five or more than up to 2 items may be defaulted. <br>
<br>
All drops including spell drops will be included toward the total count of mob drops.<br>
<br>
If only one of the major raid leaders is present then that raid leader may default loot, but may not default loot to himself/herself.<br>
<br>
Only main character members of OWD are eligible to receive defaulted loot.<br>
<br>
Epic pieces may be defaulted only on predetermined and announced defaults made by the raid coordinator.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">IV) Need Before Greed</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Items that are not defaulted will be offered in a NBG lotto.<br>
<br>
Need before greed means that in order to roll on loot, you must be willing to equip the item as your <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">primary</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> item, replacing the current item in that slot. <br>
<br>
From time to time a loot item may have high situational value. It might be a 2hand warrior weapon or a piece of resist gear etc. These loot items may be announced on nbg to be available to those who would make situational use of them, rather than requiring that the item replace your current item. <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Entering the lotto for situational use is only appropriate when it is announced as a situational item.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Class restrictions will be placed on certain items</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> so that the item will fall into the hands of the class it is best suited for. These restrictions may be posted for your awareness, but in some cases may not be available. You will not be eligible to roll on items where your class was not listed in the announced restriction, even though your class may be listed on the item in question. (Voted 4/7-14 65%) <br>
<br>
Only main characters will be allowed to roll on items. Any alternates present other than alts requested by the raid leaders will not be allowed to roll on items unless it's gravy. (Voted 4/16-21 52.5%)<br>
<br>
If an alternate is present at the raid at the request of the raid leaders to ensure the success of the raid, then that person may choose to either enter NBG rolls for droppable loot for their main character, or to enter NBG rolls for their Alt that is present. (Voted 4/7-14 69.7%)<br>
<br>
<br>
Members of &quot;allied&quot; guilds which were invited to attend as a guild are eligible to roll on NBG loot.<br>
<br>
Generally other guests are not eligible to enter NBG lotto, but if they were specifically invited to fill a needed role in the raid force at the request of a raid leader then they will be eligible for NBG loot, excluding rare spells. If you are a guest, please confirm your eligibility with a raid leader prior to the raid.<br>
<br>
Persons who have had an item defaulted or previously won an item on NBG are ineligible to enter later NBG rolls on that MOB's/zone's drops. If no-one remains eligible to claim an item on NBG then it goes to &quot;other loot&quot; and may be gravied or held for the guild bank.<br>
<br>
The guild is placing its trust in you that you will only enter NBG rolls when appropriate, and any violations of NBG policy are covered below.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">V) Other Loot</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Any Loot which is not defaulted or claimed on NBG will either be reserved for the guild bank or &quot;gravied&quot; at the discretion of the raid leaders present.<br>
<br>
All persons present are eligible to enter the lotto for any loot that is &quot;gravied.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">VI) &quot;Zone&quot; Raids</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
All drops on a zone raid from minor mobs and mini-bosses are considered as if they were one MOB, so that a person is only eligible to win one NBG item for the whole zone. On zone raids no items will be defaulted from these mobs.<br>
<br>
Major bosses are considered seperately as BGH MOBs. These would include such MOBS as Cazic Thule and Dracoliche in Fear, Innouruk in Hate, Tunare in PoG, etc.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">VII) Declaring a &quot;main&quot; character.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
In the above sections eligibility for loot is sometimes based on a guild member's status as a main or alternate character.<br>
<br>
Each real life person may have only one character that can be considered their main for purposes of the loot policy at any one time. Character's on seperate accounts are still considered alternates.<br>
<br>
A player may declare which character is the main for purposes of loot eligibility, and should do so if it would not be obvious to all persons. In order to declare a character as your main you must notify an officer who is a member of the raid team and/or post the change on the appropriate class forums.<br>
<br>
A person may change which character is their main character no more often than every 30 days. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">VIII) Loot complaints</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Complaints on loot should be made to your group leader, who will in turn pass it on to the current ML and team of raid leaders present. <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Loot complaints will NOT be made in public channels.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
The ML, in consultation with the raid team, will make a determination on the complaint and a resolution will be communicated before the loot item in question is rolled/distributed if at all possible.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">IX) Loot Ownership</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Although members are encouraged to share the wealth and pass their gear on to fellow guild members, members will not be asked or required to pass their current item down in order to receive a default or NBG item. (Voted 4/7-14 56.8%)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">X) Violations of NBG</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
With trust comes responsibility. The guild will trust you to enter only rolls which are appropriate, and that you will use the loot in a manner which is appropriate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Violations of NBG policy should be reported to the raid team.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> If a report of a violation of the NBG rules is reported, the alleged violation will be looked into by the raid leader who acted as ML at the raid where the loot item in question was won. The raid team will determine a resolution and it will be communicated to interested parties within one week.<br>
<br>
